[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hey, I have a function from an additive group <code>G</code> to a multiplicative group, <code>ℝ≥0</code> that is a homomorphism. I would like to make it a homomorphism.<br>\nWhich type should I use? Both <code>G →+ ℝ≥0</code> and <code>G →* ℝ≥0</code> don't work.</p>",
        "id": 501638300,
        "sender_full_name": "Noam Atar",
        "timestamp": 1740427801
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Multiplicative G -&gt;* ℝ≥0</code> or <code>G -&gt;+ Additive ℝ≥0</code> is the easiest way, i'd say. I don't think we have a datatype for this kind of \"exponential\" map</p>",
        "id": 501639121,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1740428061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nit: <code>ℝ≥0</code> isn't a multiplcative group</p>",
        "id": 501641481,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1740428840
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that's a fair point, but luckily that doesn't change the solution!</p>",
        "id": 501642222,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1740429070
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(and we have <code>GroupWithZero</code>, so we should be fine)</p>",
        "id": 501642295,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1740429100
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 501649427,
        "sender_full_name": "Noam Atar",
        "timestamp": 1740431608
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there something I could do to make <code>to_additive</code> do this automatically?</p>",
        "id": 501650106,
        "sender_full_name": "Noam Atar",
        "timestamp": 1740431867
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here <code>G</code> can be multiplicative or additive but <code>ℝ≥0</code> is the same</p>",
        "id": 501650215,
        "sender_full_name": "Noam Atar",
        "timestamp": 1740431892
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not that I know, unfortunately</p>",
        "id": 501655770,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1740434013
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you write only the multiplicative case then I think you get the additive one for free</p>",
        "id": 501666574,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1740437681
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(by using the multiplicative one with <code>G := Multiplicative A</code>)</p>",
        "id": 501666621,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1740437700
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK, thanks!</p>",
